“We” are the largest Belgian bank with Asian activities in Singapore, Shanghai and Hong Kong.  Each and every day our team in Asia strives to become the Preferred European Banking Partner of our domestic and European customers. To do so, we combine high professional standards and a pleasant working environment and we put our customers in the center point in everything we do. Also our internal customers!

We are looking for an enthusiastic and self-motivating talent to join our team as the Operational Risk Manager. With risk management being essential for long term sustainable operations, you can direct access to senior management via periodic or ad hoc reporting. You are also the focal person to supervise the branch’s performance of control functions in relation to operational risk.

About the job

As a Local Operational Risk Manager / Assistant Operations Manager you are in the lead for identifying, assessing and remediating operational risks; 
You closely work together with department heads in the branch to ensure the operations run smoothly and all risks are duly managed; 
You are supported and receive input from colleagues in head office and other international branches. This helps you to ensure operations comply with regulations , with KBC guidelines and with best international practices; 
You are involved in various challenging global projects that aim to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of branch’s operations; 
You contribute to implement changes to the day to day operations of the branch. You look for efficiency gains, for digitization and for increased operational collaboration between the international branches of KBC. 

About you

To join the KBC team, you need to be a good team player, with ability to communicate clearly and concisely. You must  be strong in analytical and problem-solving skills with great self-motivation and self-starting ability. You need to be familiar with regulatory requirements in banking industry and have minimum 5 years’ experience in operational risk management. Finally, need to be eager to learn and continuously develop yourself to remain future proof in a swiftly changing environment..

We offer an attractive remuneration package in line with your relevant experience and the importance of the position.  

If you feel like this position is a fit with your skill-set and expectations, please apply with a cover letter and CV (indicating your salary expectation) by email via "Apply Now". For any questions with regards to the position you can give us a call on  (852) 2879 3363.

All information received will be used for recruitment purpose only. Applicants not being invited to interview within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. All information on unsuccessful candidates will be deleted from our files within 12 months.

 

“We” are the largest Belgian bank with Asian activities in Singapore, Shanghai and Hong Kong.  Each and every day our team in Asia strives to become the Preferred European Banking Partner of our domestic and European customers. To do so, we combine high professional standards and a pleasant working environment and we put our customers in the center point in everything we do. Also our internal customers!

We are looking for an enthusiastic and self-motivating talent to join our team as the Junior Officer of Remittance and Settlement Team. You can have the exposure in full remittance and settlement process in the international banking.

